@@TJvCustomNavigationPane.MaximizedCount
Summary
  Specifies the number of buttons that are maximized.
Description
  Use MaximizedCount to programmatically set the number of pages that have a maximized button. Pages that are
  minimized (or iconic), displays a smaller button in the icon panel at the bottom of the control.

  Users can change the number of maximized buttons at run-time by adjusting the splitter (provided
  Resizable is true). When they do, the value of MaximizedCount is updated as well.
See Also
  Resizeable, TJvNavPage.Iconic
