@@TJvNavIconButton
Summary
  Button used as the small button in a TJvCustomNavigationPane.
Description
  TJvNavIconButton is the type of the button used in the icon panel on a TJvCustomNavigationPane. This
  button supports showing either an image from an image list or a drop down menu indicator consisting of
  a chevron and a drop down arrow.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvNavIconButton.ButtonType
Summary
  Specifies the visual appearance of the button.
Description
  Use ButtonType to specify the visual appearance of the button. If ButtonType is nibDropDown, the button
  displays a chevron and a drop down arrow. If ButtonType is nibImgae, the button displays an image
  from the Images image list.
See Also
  Images, ImageIndex
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvNavIconButton.Colors
Summary
  Contains the color settings of the control.
Description
  Use the subproperties of Colors to specify the visual appearance of the control. Colors has several different
  sub colors. Since Colors is a general color class, it may contain colors not used by the control.
See Also
  TJvNavPaneStyleManager
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvNavIconButton.ImageIndex
Summary
  Specifies the image to display.
Description
  Set ImageIndex to a value between 0 and Images.Count - 1 to display an image in the control.

  You will also need to assign an image list to the Images property and set ButtonType to nibImage for
  the button to display the image.
See Also
  ButtonType, Images
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvNavIconButton.Images
Summary
  Specifies the images to use when displaying an image in the control.
Description
  Assign an image list to Images to specify the images to use when displaying an image in the button. The actual image
  to display is determined by the ImageIndex property. An image is only displayed when ButtonType is set to nibImage.
See Also
  ImageIndex, ButtonType
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
